She’s a warrior - but more importantly, she’s a role model for the next generation of Native Americans.

In 2022 @naethrowsheavyrock became the first Native American woman to win a medal at the World Athletics Championships. 

“It was the most rewarding, honouring, humbling moment when it actually arrived.” – but her bronze medal in the hammer throw was worth so much more.

📝 Warrior, by Janee’ Kassanavoid 🔗 #linkinbio

UPGRADED 🥈 x 🇺🇸 x 🔨

a WIN, not only for me but a WIN for my coach, my family, and my nation. Comanche Nation. I couldn’t have done this without the strength, the power, and the resilience of my people behind me. This journey has taken me places I’ve never imagined possible but it has truly been a dream come true. ✨

SEE ME, SEE US. 🪶🤍
